<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Whateer" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Whate'er</orth> (followed by the indicative, though often followed by <emph>be;</emph> cf. <emph>Be</emph>), 1) no matter what; this or that or any thing that; substantively: <cit><quote>he strikes w. is in his way,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 623" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 623</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>do w. thou wilt,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 19.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 19, 6</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>w. thy thoughts be,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 5.93.11" default="NO" valid="yes">93, 11</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.151" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. V, 4, 151</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.109" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 109</bibl> (<emph>w. you are,</emph> i. e. savage or civil). <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.382.155" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 382</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.4.36" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 4, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.1.37" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.28" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.5.38" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 5, 38</bibl> (Qq <emph>be,</emph> Ff <emph>am</emph>). <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.71" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 71</bibl> (Ff <emph>whatever</emph>). <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.37" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.38" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 77</bibl> (<emph>therefore Achilles: but w., know this;</emph> i. e. w. your name may be). <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.195" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 195</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 1, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.4.29" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.6.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 6, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 3.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. III, 2, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 10</bibl> etc. Adjectively: <cit><quote>w. occasion keeps him from us now,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 3</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) == whoever: <cit><quote>I am to get a man, -- w. he be, it skills not much,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.133" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 133</bibl></cit> (perhaps == of what kind soever).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>